  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "131d638c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The results confirm that the `mixed` mode loads approximately twice as many rows as `v1` or `v2`.\n",
    "\n",
    "This validates that both dataset versions are combined correctly during the read process.\n",
    "\n",
    "The benchmark therefore confirms that backward-compatible reads work as expected with the current schema evolution scenario."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1f966fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Query runtime\n",
    "\n",
    "The next objective was evaluating the runtime cost of reading multiple schema versions together.\n",
    "\n",
    "The figure below compares query runtime for:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `v1`\n",
    "- `v2`\n",
    "- `mixed`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "2af29961",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pivot_query = df.pivot(\n",
    "    index=\"dataset_size_label\",\n",
    "    columns=\"mode\",\n",
    "    values=\"query_time_s\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot_query = pivot_query.loc[[\"S\", \"M\", \"L\"]]\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot_query.plot(kind=\"bar\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Query runtime by dataset size and mode\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Dataset size\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Query runtime (seconds)\")\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e8c15359",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The benchmark shows that the `mixed` mode generally requires more processing than reading a single dataset version.\n",
    "\n",
    "This behavior is expected because the reader must:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. load both dataset versions;\n",
    "2. align schemas;\n",
    "3. concatenate both tables;\n",
    "4. execute the analytics query.\n",
    "\n",
    "The additional cost of the `mixed` mode becomes more visible for the largest benchmark configuration (`L`).\n",
    "\n",
    "At the same time, the benchmark also shows some runtime variation between configurations. For example, the `S` benchmark does not follow a perfectly linear trend. Since the benchmark was executed locally and only once per setup, small variations remain expected."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7aaac085",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Object layout and storage behavior\n",
    "\n",
    "Each dataset version is stored in a separate object-storage prefix inside the MinIO bucket.\n",
    "\n",
    "The benchmark therefore makes it possible to verify that the reader accesses the expected objects during execution."
